The paper discusses computer-based annotation systems, which are primarily used in human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and natural language processing (cs.CL) research. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques (cs.DL) for annotation systems and the sharing of annotations through repositories (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of current annotation systems, which could be addressed through advancements in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG).
